FT  14 JUN 93 / Home set ablaze in Bavaria
Two unknown assailants set fire to the farmhouse home of a Turkish family in
Bavaria while the occupants were away on holiday, police said yesterday,
Reuter reports from Munich.
The police in the town of Steinfeld said no motive for the attack was
immediately clear. Similar fire bombings of foreigners' homes have surged
since five Turkish women and children were killed in an arson attack on May
29 in Solingen.
